Description: Fragment of double handle at neck join from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; some large white inclusions; no slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and perhaps club symbol.
Curator's comments: Other similar stamps have alpha and delta to left of club. Drawn by Petrie in his Journal, 1884-5, p.188a, 15.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0129)
